{{Quote|Get a '''medpack''' for Biggs, Uncle Owen... an' have Aunt Beru call out the local militia '''fast!'''|Luke Skywalker|<ref name="SW17">[[Star Wars (1977) 17|''Star Wars'' (1977) 17]]</ref>}}
The '''Tatooine militia''', sometimes referred to as the '''Mos Eisley Militia''',<ref name="Betwixt">{{WEGCite|story=There's Many a Slip Betwixt Cup and Lip|book=Mos Eisley Adventure Set}}</ref> was a loosely organized volunteer organization of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] colonists who patrolled the deserts in [[Landspeeder/Legends|landspeeders]] and [[Swoop/Legends|swoops]] watching out for [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raider]] raids, which they would band together to fight off. At one time it had four full-time members, but by [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] all full-time members were transferred to the [[Mos Eisley Police Authority|Mos Eisley police]]. The militia could still call on up to fifty individuals at any given time to deal with emergencies.<ref name="GG7" />

Weeks after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], a dozen militia confronted the [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|Heroes of Yavin]] as they tried to escape [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]].<ref name="SW Missions 6">''[[Star Wars Missions 6: The Search for Grubba the Hutt]]''</ref>

Right after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], the militia under the command of [[Predne Balu]] became engaged in the [[Rebellion on Tatooine]].<ref name="Sand">{{WEGCite|book=Mos Eisley Adventure Set|story=A Line in the Sand...}}</ref>

==Equipment==
They wore tan and gray battle armor.

